episodes.title: Bret Michaels
episodes.plot: Sal, Q and Murr are crashing and burning into the product displays and hiding in tight spaces, but one of them must face the music with celebrity guest Bret Michaels.

episodes.title: Post Malone
episodes.plot: The jokers give unsolicited etiquette advice and live tape strange product reviews; one lucky joker takes all the blame for celebrity guest Post Malone

episodes.title: Anthony Davis
episodes.plot: From working remotely to pitching unconventional business ideas with Steve Byrne, one Joker has a shot at winning a pair of highly sought-after sneakers thanks to NBA star Anthony Davis.

episodes.title: John Mayer
episodes.plot: Joined by John Mayer, the Jokers must convince unsuspecting temps to accompany them to a business dinner, and the losing Joker has to face the wrath of angry Mayer fans in a humiliating punishment.

episodes.title: Kesha
episodes.plot: Sal, Q, and Murr fall head over heels for someone they just met; a heated debate with pro wrestler MJF; a Joker discovers an untapped clairvoyant talent they possess with Kesha.

episodes.title: Sideline Smack Talk
episodes.plot: A special episode hosted by Casey Jost and former NFL player Eddie Jackson as they spend time reviewing nail-biting clips of never-before-seen moments from Season 10.

episodes.title: Paul Scheer
episodes.plot: Unable to pull off this week's pickleball and coffee shop challenges, the losing Jokers are forced to participate in an overseas game show hosted by Paul Scheer.

episodes.title: Kal Penn
episodes.plot: The jokers are posing as salesmen and must sell their bizarre products to focus group participants, then attempt a challenge that turns out to be a mouthful.

episodes.title: Bruce Campbell
episodes.plot: The jokers are dishing out as waiters and later grilled by news anchor Rosanna Scotto; the losing joker is in for a horrific treat.

episodes.title: Blake Anderson
episodes.plot: Q, Sal, and Murr pose as cash grabby waiters, and later as embarrassing parents. After, the losing Joker is forced into a far-out focus group punishment with special guest, and so-called Ganja Weasel, Blake Anderson.
